<br>
Fifty, if not more people, cancelled all their real life appointments and reserved the entire weekend just to be able to participate in this raid. When the time was there and everyone was gathered at Greater Faydark, we found out that a guild called Legion of the Royal Dragoon (aka Lords) did not respect our reservation, even had a /guildmotd urging their members to arrive at Fear before LoM did, so that they could steal our reservation and claim the plane theirs.<br>
<br>
Not even one minute had passed after we inserted into Hate, until Lords members started scolding at us, cursing at us and carrying out personal attacks on us. Lords even called a GM to ask Verant to disband our guild for not respecting their Blitzkrieg in Hate. Our raid leader was summoned to Qeynos Catacombs to talk things over with Lords. The result of this conversation, that lasted 1-1.5 hours while the entire guild was waiting for instructions, was that the GM's decided to let us share the plane. Though the plane was rightfully ours, LoM agreed to sharing the plane, as the GM's did not give us any other choice.<br>
<br>
We continued insertion, only to be bashed, cursed and threatened again by Lords. However, we persisted and did not answer these attacks. Our guild policy is, and has always been, that whenever we are attacked, we smile... and walk away. However, several hours later, it turned out that the plane was too smal for the both of us. The Lords camp would die by trains caused by our camp (not intentionally) and our camp would die by trains caused by Lords.<br>
<br>
In the end, we thought it was best to stop the entire operation, smile... and walk away. We left the plane, 2000 plat of Hate stones poorer. I will not mention the incredible loss of experience and time (including 3 weeks of planning). Not to forget the incredible frustration of our guild members and all members from other guilds that were invited because of these great injustice.<br>
<br>
Golom, the guild leader of Lords, told us he was looking forward to the day on which we would be able to share a beer and laugh about all this. I have one advice for GoloM:<br>
<br>
Make sure your reservation at the bar gets respected. It might be taken by another guild.<br>
<br>
More information on this incident will be posted by one of our guild members soon, including screenshots and proof.<br>
<br>
What follows is just my decision and my decision alone:<br>
<br>
All Lords members I will meet in this game from now on, will, as long as they wear their Lords tag:<br>
<br>
- Not get ports<br>
- Not get TL's<br>
- Not get me in their group<br>
- Not get their corpses dragged by me<br>
- Not get any reply to their tells<br>
<br>
Instead, I will smile... and walk away.<br>
<br>
Yomarbalthasar Magnhyrrturbam, level 51 wizard, Legends of Marr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uctiz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ctiz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Loading Please Wait....</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#333333>(9/23/01 5:39:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Legion of the Royal Dragoon and their idea of fair game </span><hr size=1> Dont want to sound like an ass or anything, but......  We do not have a reservation system on this server.  You can post your intent that you want to go somewhere on a certain date, but all the guilds have agreed and respected FCFS policy.  I think the only reason this section of the board is up, is to try and avoid conflicts, such as what you are talking about.  But, that still does not reserve the Plane for your guild, if another guild beats you into the Plane.  If we were going to have a reservation system, I am pretty sure we would have a calander up, like back on The Rathe *shiver*.<br>
